{"parse":{"title":"Andrea Batista Schlesinger","pageid":11610978,"revid":798474897,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-BLP_sources\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">biography of a living person</a> <b>needs additional <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">citations</a> for <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">verification</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\">reliable sources</a>. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>, especially if potentially <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Libel\" title=\"Wikipedia:Libel\">libelous</a> or harmful.</span>  <small><i>(November 2014)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Andrea Batista Schlesinger</b> (born October 27, 1976, <a href=\"/wiki/Brooklyn\" title=\"Brooklyn\">Brooklyn</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_(state)\" title=\"New York (state)\">New York</a>, United States) is an American <a href=\"/wiki/Political_writer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Political writer\">political writer</a> and campaigner. She was until 2009 the executive director of the <a href=\"/wiki/Drum_Major_Institute\" title=\"Drum Major Institute\">Drum Major Institute</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Background\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Background</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Awards_and_recognition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards and recognition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Background\">Background</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Batista_Schlesinger&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Background\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Schlesinger was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York, by a Dominican mother and a Jewish father. She grew up in <a href=\"/wiki/Sea_Gate,_Brooklyn\" title=\"Sea Gate, Brooklyn\">Sea Gate, Brooklyn</a>. She was appointed as the student representative to the <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City_Board_of_Education\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York City Board of Education\">New York City Board of Education</a>, and later studied <a href=\"/wiki/Public_policy\" title=\"Public policy\">public policy</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Chicago\" title=\"University of Chicago\">University of Chicago</a>.\n</p><p>She directed a national campaign to engage college students in the discussion on the future of <a href=\"/wiki/Social_Security_(United_States)\" title=\"Social Security (United States)\">Social Security</a> for the <a href=\"/wiki/Pew_Charitable_Trusts\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pew Charitable Trusts\">Pew Charitable Trusts</a>,<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (November 2014)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> and served as Director of Public Relations of <a href=\"/wiki/Teach_For_America\" title=\"Teach For America\">Teach For America</a> before working as the education advisor to <a href=\"/wiki/Bronx\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bronx\">Bronx</a> Borough President <a href=\"/wiki/Fernando_Ferrer\" title=\"Fernando Ferrer\">Fernando Ferrer</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (November 2014)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p><p>From 2002 to 2009, Schlesinger led the Drum Major Institute, a <a href=\"/wiki/Think-tank\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Think-tank\">think-tank</a> founded by an advisor to <a href=\"/wiki/Dr._Martin_Luther_King,_Jr.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.\">Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.</a> during the <a href=\"/wiki/Civil_Rights_Movement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Civil Rights Movement\">Civil Rights Movement</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (November 2014)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> During her tenure as executive director, DMI released several policy papers to national audiences.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> including: Congress at the Midterm: Their Middle-Class Record <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and Principles for an Immigration Policy to Strengthen and Expand the American Middle Class.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> In February 2009, she took leave from that position to work as a policy adviser to the re-election campaign of <a href=\"/wiki/Mayor_of_New_York_City\" title=\"Mayor of New York City\">Mayor of New York City</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Bloomberg\" title=\"Michael Bloomberg\">Michael Bloomberg</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> She is currently serving as a board member for <a href=\"/wiki/The_New_York_Women%27s_Foundation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The New York Women&#39;s Foundation\">The New York Women's Foundation</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Batista_Schlesinger&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-BLP_unsourced\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section of a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">biography of a living person</a> <b>does not <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">include</a> any <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">references or sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\">reliable sources</a>. Contentious material about living people that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>.<br /><small><span class=\"plainlinks\"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22&amp;num=50\">\"Andrea Batista Schlesinger\"</a>&#160;\u2013&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+-wikipedia\">news</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers\">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+-wikipedia\">books</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22\">scholar</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on\">JSTOR</a></span></small></span>  <small><i>(November 2014)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Schlesinger's work has been published in <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Newsday\" title=\"New York Newsday\">New York Newsday</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Crains_New_York_Business\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crains New York Business\">Crains New York Business</a></i>, the Mississippi <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sun_Herald\" title=\"Sun Herald\">Sun Herald</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Daily_News\" title=\"New York Daily News\">New York Daily News</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Alternet.com\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alternet.com\">Alternet.com</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tom_Paine.com&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Tom Paine.com (page does not exist)\">Tom Paine.com</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Sun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Sun\">New York Sun</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Colorlines_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Colorlines Magazine (page does not exist)\">Colorlines Magazine</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Chief-Leader\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Chief-Leader\">The Chief-Leader</a></i>, and <i><a href=\"/wiki/City_Limits_Magazine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"City Limits Magazine\">City Limits Magazine</a></i>. She is also a contributor to <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Huffington_Post\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Huffington Post\">The Huffington Post</a></i> and is on the Editorial Board at <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Nation\" title=\"The Nation\">The Nation</a></i>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards_and_recognition\">Awards and recognition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Batista_Schlesinger&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Awards and recognition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-BLP_unsourced\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"40\" data-file-height=\"40\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This section of a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons\" title=\"Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons\">biography of a living person</a> <b>does not <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citing sources\">include</a> any <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">references or sources</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help by adding <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources\" title=\"Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources\">reliable sources</a>. Contentious material about living people that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>.<br /><small><span class=\"plainlinks\"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22&amp;num=50\">\"Andrea Batista Schlesinger\"</a>&#160;\u2013&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+-wikipedia\">news</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers\">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22+-wikipedia\">books</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22\">scholar</a>&#160;<b>\u00b7</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Andrea+Batista+Schlesinger%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on\">JSTOR</a></span></small></span>  <small><i>(November 2014)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<ul><li>Awarded \u201c40 under 40 Rising Star\u201d by <i><a href=\"/wiki/Crain%27s_New_York_Business\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crain&#39;s New York Business\">Crain's New York Business</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Named \u201c35 under 40 Rising Stars, The Next Generation of Political Leaders in New York\u201d by <i>City Hall Newspaper</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Recipient of <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=LatinaPAC&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"LatinaPAC (page does not exist)\">LatinaPAC</a>'s Dolores Huerta Award for \"making great strides in promoting progress in our community\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Named \u201cExpert of the Week\u201d by <a href=\"/wiki/Fenton_Communications\" title=\"Fenton Communications\">Fenton Communications</a>' and the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=White_House_Project&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"White House Project (page does not exist)\">White House Project</a>\u2019s \"SheSource\" program, a project promoting left-wing women policy experts to television and radio.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (November 2014)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrea_Batista_Schlesinger&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.pbs.org/now/politics/middleclassoverview.html\">\"NOW. Politics &amp; Economy. Who is the Middle Class? Overview\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PBS\" title=\"PBS\">PBS</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">5 November</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=NOW.+Politics+%26+Economy.+Who+is+the+Middle+Class%3F+Overview&amp;rft.pub=PBS&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fnow%2Fpolitics%2Fmiddleclassoverview.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Batista+Schlesinger\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20071022103406/http://www.californiaprogressreport.com/2007/01/the_drum_major.html\">\"The Drum Major Institute 2006 Year in Review is our site of the day\"</a>. Drum Major Institute. 16 January 2007. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.californiaprogressreport.com/2007/01/the_drum_major.html\">the original</a> on 22 October 2007.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Drum+Major+Institute+2006+Year+in+Review+is+our+site+of+the+day&amp;rft.pub=Drum+Major+Institute&amp;rft.date=2007-01-16&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.californiaprogressreport.com%2F2007%2F01%2Fthe_drum_major.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrea+Batista+Schlesinger\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> </span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.drummajorinstitute.org/congress/\">[1]</a>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080703213719/http://www.drummajorinstitute.org/congress/\">Archived</a> July 3, 2008, at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</